page.title: 15DAY IN LIFE OF CATHERINE
page.content: AT FOUR OR FIVE O'CLOCK IN THE MORNING I LET MUFFIN IN THROUGH THE WINDOW IF HE IS NOT ALREADY ON MY BED. AT SIX O'CLOCK I AM ALLOWED TO PRACTISE MY INSTRUMENT SO I PRACTISE THE PIANO. WHEN I HAVE DONE ALL MY PIECES AND WORKED THROUGH MY SCALE BOOK I GET DRESSED. IF MUM AND DAD ARE STILL ASLEEP I DO SOME THEORY AND FEED MUFFIN.BY THAT TIME THEY ARE BOUND TO BE AWAKE. WE HAVE OUR BREAKFAST. IF IT'S WARM WE HAVE IT OUTSIDE ON THE BALCONY. IF THERE IS STILL TIME TO PRACTISE THE OBOE I PRACTISE IT, IF NOT I PRACTISE IT AFTER SCHOOL. THEN I GO TO SCHOOL. AFTER SCHOOL I HAVE A SNACK BEFORE GOING TO OBOE AND PIANO THE ROOM I PLAY THE OBOE IN IS REALLY NICE FOR PLAYING THE OBOE. MRS SIMMS TEACHES ME THE OBOE.
